{"TopicId":156149,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"ideal orbit for telescope?","CreatedByName":"Carrot","CreatedById":154743,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-08T04:52:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Carrot","CreatedById":154743,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-08T04:52:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just downloaded a space telescope mod which has 2 telescopes. I am wondering where should I put them on? polar orbit or equator orbit or a 45 degrees orbit? Around kerbin or around the sun? Thanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ohm is Futile","CreatedById":172721,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-08T05:03:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222948463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486529528\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154743\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Carrot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Carrot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just downloaded a space telescope mod which has 2 telescopes. I am wondering where should I put them on? polar orbit or equator orbit or a 45 degrees orbit? Around kerbin or around the sun? Thanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPolar orbits are the only orbits that will guarantee you will cover just about all of a body\u0027s surface. As for distance/orbiting